summary: An Ordinance providing for the improvement of Olympic Way, in the City of Seattle, from Eighth Avenue West to Tenth Avenue, by constructing concrete walks thereon, together with all necessary wooden curbs, gutters and crosswalks, in accordance with Resolution No. 540 of the City Council of the City of Seattle, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Payment by Bonds," as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle
